original_title: Richmond: Annadale Road - Arthur Kill Road
text:
(1)
Annadale Road, west side, south of Arthur Kill Road (about 400 yards). This house was the residence of A. Ferugson (1874), J. Wegener (1887), and Martin Keppler (1898 to 1917). The dates refer to maps on which the owners' names appear.

June 21, 1926.

By Wm. T. Davis
through P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, as seen from a different angle.

June 21, 1926.

By Wm. T. Davis
through P. L. Sperr.

original_title: Richmond: Arthur Kill Road - Annadale Road
text:
Arthur Kill Road, north side, between Annadale and Woodrow Roads (vantage point), showing the Dolan Brick Works on Richmond Creek. The view is northeastward. View 3 shows the coal sheds.

View 1: May 30, 1932
View 2: May 22, 1936
View 3: Oct. 6, 1928

P. L. Sperr

original_title: Richmond: Arthur Kill Road - Annadale Road
text:
Arthur Kill Road, north side, at Annadale Road (vantage point), showing a view northeastward across the Fresh Kills marshes and the Richmond Avenue bridge over Richmond Creek.

May 22, 1936.

P.L. Sperr

original_title: Richmond: Arthur Kill Road - Annadale Road
text:
Arthur Kill Road, at the S.W. corner of Annadale Road, showing the hotel which belonged to F. J. Clancy (1917). In 1907 it was owned by Kate H. Agne. The dates refer to maps on which the owners' names appear.

May 22, 1936

P. L. Sperr
